				<h2>About Me</h2>
				<p>
					Hi, my name's Zarcka! What do you think about it?
					<br>
					I am someone who is rather creative, more or less silly, and who has a soft spot for anything of cute or adorable such as cats :3, dogs, and plushies ^-^. I find pleasure in learning about things that I am passionate about or simply interested in, and being able to better my understanding. Some of those things are &#8212; programming: I have been teaching myself programming for a few years by now and whilst I have become more or less good at it, I still have a lot to improve on and much more to learn, and so as of the time of writing, I am learning Haskell, a functional programming language, to improve as a programmer while expanding my skillset; mathematics: I am someone of passionate about mathematics and I have been learning about differentiation for a little while from online resources such as the '<a href="https://www.3blue1brown.com/topics/calculus" target="_blank">Essence of Calculus</a>' by <a href="https://www.3blue1brown.com" target="_blank">3Blue1Brown</a> and have more recently started learning on integration from the same course, and further on, I would like to learn more on linear algebra; German: I am learning German on my own from books, online resources, and a with a little help from my lovely, multilingual friend who also has their own website: <a href="https://leaf.moe" target="_blank">https://leaf.moe</a>, and as I am still early on in my learning, I often make mistakes and even though they can be discouraging, I am determined and do not plan on giving up anytime soon; and DIY: as I like repairing and crafting little things, DIY became an interest of mine, and an example of me doing DIY was when I used a pen cap as a replacement for the missing tip of my umbrella. Moreover, I am an artist and I draw on rare occasions as I am busy with studies and working on other projects such as this one. But regardless of that, I still would like to draw more often as I want to complete some of my unfinished artworks especially my masterpiece. Furthermore, I enjoy playing osu!, a rythm game, and more specifically osu!mania 4k, a game mode of osu!, as I have been improving quite a lot at it and as I find it more enjoyable than the standard game mode. And lastly, I enjoy playing around with my voice by pitching it higher, meowing or making other weird sounds but most of the time, I prefer to meow and I have been able to improve quite a lot, I now can meow more easily at will and better modulate it.
				</p>
				<p>
					Starting with programming, I got into programming at a young age due to my fascination for computers and electronics. At first, I attempted to learn python with little success, then my second attempt was at learning at C++ &#8212; and you can guess how well did that went. Even though I had no prior experience to low-level programming, I was quite ambitious and even created a little group named the 'C++ Grave' as I said that I would bury myself there if I failed to learn C++, and that this grave would provide guidance and caution to those who dare follow the same path. However, it would not only turn out to be a place to talk about my journey but also a place to have a casual chat and discuss about life and many other things &#8212; cooking included. I got to spend a fun and memorable time with some nice people and I am quite thankful to them for those memories. Even though my adventure had unfortunately ended (and that I am now buried and became a ghost), the history of this group would not end so soon, but unfortunately, it is too long to write here in details. After I have given up C++, I moved to front-end development where I would learn about HTML, CSS, JS, JS-frameworks, and a little web designing skills alongside other things. Nevertheless, I still attempt to learn a new programming language and this time around, it is Haskell &#8212; a functional programming language. And later on, I would like to move to other things like game development, and maybe also learn about electronics and even about robotics.
				</p>
				<p>
					Following with art, I draw occasionally using pen or pencil on A3 or A4 paper. I originally used pencil but now pen is preferred for drawing but not yet for writing; pen is my preferred option as it doesn't need to be sharpened like pencil does but I am still improving at drawing with pen and better incorporating colours into my art while also learning about the different types of pen and inks, and their properties. A4 paper is the size of paper I originally began with and is still my preferred option as I am habited to drawing on A4 paper and as it takes less time to complete compared to A3 paper, but by 'less time', I do not mean 1 or 2 weeks; a detailed A4 drawing can take up to a month or more depnding on the size of the drawing, the level of details and how regurlarly I work on the drawing. So a full detailed A3 drawing would take half a year or more to be completed, and this is why you won't see new drawings often. Before my journey towards abstract art, I did draw but I was replicating other people's artworks from a mobile phone screen onto paper using pencil, and this may have inadvertently given me an advantage when I began doing abstract art. My journey began when I met a dear friend of mine who is an amazing artist (<a href="https://ashnscar21.carrd.co/" target="_blank">Ash's website</a>), and they showed an artwork of theirs to me which made me jealous so I started watching a tutorial but then deviated from it as I explored and did my own things. A few years later, my specialty is now abstract art, I am here writing about my way of doing art and I am no more as jealous of their artworks or other people's artworks as much as before. I thank them for giving me the spark of motivation that started my journey and the determination that kept me going till this day, so if you have the time, you should take a look at <a href="https://ashnscar21coms.carrd.co/#portfolio" target="_blank">their portfolio</a> and also check their other <a href="https://ashnscar21mediapage.carrd.co/" target="_blank">social media</a> especially the discord server, <a href="https://discord.gg/fhN7AYD6Yq" target="_blank">Ash's Cafe | Community Server</a>, as I am the host of Question of the Day (and Question of the Night) in this server, and you can meet me there.
				</p>
				<p>
					Lastly, osu! &#8212; my favourite rythm game (profile: <a href="https://osu.ppy.sh/users/32690558" target="_blank">Zarcka</a>). I began to play in January of 2023 and at first, it took me a while to get used to the mechanics of <a href="https://osu.ppy.sh/wiki/en/Game_Mode#osu!" target="_blank">osu!</a> (game mode). After having gotten used to osu! mechanics, I kept playing for more than a year using keyboard and mouse, and I am still playing and improving while having fun. And at the time of writing, I can play <a href="https://osu.ppy.sh/wiki/en/Beatmap/Difficulty" target="_blank">difficulties</a> up to 4 stars at an AR of around 9. Furthermore, I am also an <a href="https://osu.ppy.sh/wiki/en/Game_Mode#osu!mania" target="_blank">osu!mania</a> [4K, 6K, 7K] player. I began playing osu!mania as my performance on osu! began to plateau and I was becoming increasingly frustrated at it, so I took a break from osu! and focused on osu!mania; I improved quite rapidly and had a lot of fun, the became curious so I tried out 6K and later on 7K. The highest difficulty I can play on osu!mania 4K: 3.2 stars; 6K and 7K: 2 stars. Last but not least, I really like playing both osu! and osu!mania, and osu! is my favourite rythm game and have made my love for rythm games even stronger. I also began playing Phigros (it's a nightmare of its own) as it caught my interest and as it has some challenging game mechanics that put my skills to the test; and I have been having fun playing Phigros even though I struggle to hit some note types.
				</p>
